Note:
Runa Standard Library: Intelligent Cost Optimization Module

Provides AI-powered cost analysis and optimization for cloud infrastructure across
all providers. Implements advanced cost analytics, automated optimization recommendations,
intelligent resource rightsizing, and comprehensive cost governance with predictive
cost modeling and automated cost control mechanisms.

Features:
- AI-powered cost analysis with machine learning-based optimization
- Real-time cost anomaly detection and alerting
- Automated resource rightsizing based on usage patterns
- Reserved instance and savings plan optimization
- Spot instance and preemptible VM opportunity identification
- Storage cost optimization with intelligent tiering
- Cross-cloud cost comparison and optimization
- Automated cost governance with budget enforcement
- Predictive cost modeling and forecasting
- Comprehensive cost reporting and analytics
:End Note

Import "cloud/multi_cloud_orchestrator" as orchestrator

Note: Core Cost Optimization Types
Type called "CloudAccountData":
    account_id as String
    provider as orchestrator.CloudProvider
    monthly_spend as Float
    resource_inventory as List[orchestrator.MultiCloudResource]
    billing_history as List[BillingDataPoint]
    usage_patterns as Dictionary[String, UsagePattern]
    budget_constraints as BudgetConstraints
    cost_allocation_tags as Dictionary[String, String]

Type called "BillingDataPoint":
    timestamp as Integer
    total_cost as Float
    cost_by_service as Dictionary[String, Float]
    cost_by_region as Dictionary[String, Float]
    usage_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]
    cost_trends as Dictionary[String, Float]

Type called "UsagePattern":
    resource_id as String
    resource_type as orchestrator.ResourceType
    average_utilization as Float
    peak_utilization as Float
    utilization_variance as Float
    usage_schedule as UsageSchedule
    seasonal_patterns as List[SeasonalPattern]
    cost_efficiency_score as Float

Type called "CostOptimizationReport":
    account_id as String
    current_monthly_spend as Float
    potential_monthly_savings as Float
    savings_percentage as Float
    optimization_actions as List[OptimizationAction]
    implementation_roadmap as ImplementationRoadmap
    roi_analysis as ROIAnalysis
    risk_assessment as OptimizationRiskAssessment
    executive_summary as CostOptimizationSummary

Type called "OptimizationAction":
    action_id as String
    action_type as OptimizationActionType
    affected_resource as String
    current_configuration as Dictionary[String, Any]
    recommended_configuration as Dictionary[String, Any]
    estimated_monthly_savings as Float
    implementation_complexity as ComplexityLevel
    risk_level as RiskLevel
    prerequisites as List[String]
    implementation_steps as List[String]

Type OptimizationActionType is:
    | RIGHTSIZING
    | RESERVED_INSTANCE_PURCHASE
    | SPOT_INSTANCE_MIGRATION
    | STORAGE_TIER_OPTIMIZATION
    | UNUSED_RESOURCE_CLEANUP
    | SCHEDULE_BASED_SCALING
    | CROSS_CLOUD_MIGRATION
    | ARCHITECTURE_OPTIMIZATION

Type ComplexityLevel is:
    | LOW
    | MEDIUM
    | HIGH
    | VERY_HIGH

Type RiskLevel is:
    | MINIMAL
    | LOW
    | MEDIUM
    | HIGH
    | CRITICAL

Note: AI-Powered Cost Analysis Engine
Process called "analyze_cost_optimization_opportunities" that takes account_data as CloudAccountData returns CostOptimizationReport:
    Note: AI-powered cost analysis with actionable optimization recommendations
    Let analysis_context be create_cost_analysis_context with account_data as account_data
    
    Note: Parallel analysis of different optimization opportunities
    Let usage_patterns be analyze_resource_usage_patterns with data as account_data and context as analysis_context
    Let cost_anomalies be detect_cost_anomalies with data as account_data and context as analysis_context
    Let rightsizing_opportunities be identify_rightsizing_opportunities with patterns as usage_patterns and data as account_data
    Let reserved_instance_recommendations be analyze_reserved_instance_opportunities with data as account_data and patterns as usage_patterns
    Let spot_instance_opportunities be identify_spot_instance_opportunities with data as account_data and patterns as usage_patterns
    Let storage_optimization be analyze_storage_optimization with data as account_data and patterns as usage_patterns
    Let unused_resource_analysis be identify_unused_resources with data as account_data and patterns as usage_patterns
    Let architecture_optimization be analyze_architecture_optimization with data as account_data and patterns as usage_patterns
    
    Note: Calculate total potential savings
    Let total_potential_savings be calculate_total_savings with:
        rightsizing_savings as rightsizing_opportunities["potential_savings"]
        reserved_instance_savings as reserved_instance_recommendations["potential_savings"]
        spot_instance_savings as spot_instance_opportunities["potential_savings"]
        storage_savings as storage_optimization["potential_savings"]
        unused_resource_savings as unused_resource_analysis["potential_savings"]
        architecture_savings as architecture_optimization["potential_savings"]
    
    Note: Prioritize optimizations by impact and feasibility
    Let optimization_priority_queue be prioritize_optimizations_by_impact with:
        rightsizing as rightsizing_opportunities
        reserved_instances as reserved_instance_recommendations
        spot_instances as spot_instance_opportunities
        storage as storage_optimization
        unused_resources as unused_resource_analysis
        architecture as architecture_optimization
    
    Note: Create implementation roadmap
    Let implementation_roadmap be create_cost_optimization_roadmap with:
        actions as optimization_priority_queue
        account_data as account_data
        analysis_context as analysis_context
    
    Note: Perform ROI analysis
    Let roi_analysis be calculate_optimization_roi with:
        actions as optimization_priority_queue
        current_spend as account_data["monthly_spend"]
        implementation_roadmap as implementation_roadmap
    
    Return CostOptimizationReport with:
        account_id as account_data["account_id"]
        current_monthly_spend as account_data["monthly_spend"]
        potential_monthly_savings as total_potential_savings
        savings_percentage as (total_potential_savings divided by account_data["monthly_spend"]) times 100.0
        optimization_actions as optimization_priority_queue
        implementation_roadmap as implementation_roadmap
        roi_analysis as roi_analysis
        risk_assessment as assess_optimization_risks with actions as optimization_priority_queue
        executive_summary as generate_cost_optimization_executive_summary with:
            current_spend as account_data["monthly_spend"]
            potential_savings as total_potential_savings
            top_actions as take_first_n with list as optimization_priority_queue and n as 5
            roi as roi_analysis

Process called "identify_rightsizing_opportunities" that takes patterns as Dictionary[String, UsagePattern] and data as CloudAccountData returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Identify compute resources that can be rightsized for cost optimization
    Let rightsizing_recommendations be list containing
    Let total_potential_savings be 0.0
    
    For each resource_id in keys of patterns:
        Let pattern be patterns[resource_id]
        Let resource be find_resource_by_id with resources as data["resource_inventory"] and id as resource_id
        
        If resource is not None and (resource["resource_type"] is equal to orchestrator.COMPUTE_INSTANCE):
            Let rightsizing_analysis be analyze_compute_rightsizing with:
                resource as resource
                pattern as pattern
                pricing_data as get_pricing_data with provider as resource["provider"] and region as resource["region"]
            
            If rightsizing_analysis["recommendation"] is not equal to "no_change":
                Let optimization_action be OptimizationAction with:
                    action_id as generate_action_id
                    action_type as RIGHTSIZING
                    affected_resource as resource_id
                    current_configuration as extract_current_configuration with resource as resource
                    recommended_configuration as rightsizing_analysis["recommended_configuration"]
                    estimated_monthly_savings as rightsizing_analysis["monthly_savings"]
                    implementation_complexity as rightsizing_analysis["complexity"]
                    risk_level as rightsizing_analysis["risk_level"]
                    prerequisites as rightsizing_analysis["prerequisites"]
                    implementation_steps as generate_rightsizing_steps with analysis as rightsizing_analysis
                
                Add optimization_action to rightsizing_recommendations
                Set total_potential_savings to total_potential_savings plus rightsizing_analysis["monthly_savings"]
    
    Return dictionary with:
        "recommendations" as rightsizing_recommendations
        "potential_savings" as total_potential_savings
        "affected_resources" as length of rightsizing_recommendations
        "analysis_metadata" as create_analysis_metadata with type as "rightsizing"

Process called "analyze_compute_rightsizing" that takes resource as orchestrator.MultiCloudResource and pattern as UsagePattern and pricing_data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Analyze individual compute resource for rightsizing opportunities
    Let current_instance_type be resource["configuration"]["instance_type"]
    Let current_specs be get_instance_specifications with instance_type as current_instance_type and provider as resource["provider"]
    
    Note: Analyze utilization patterns
    Let cpu_utilization be pattern["average_utilization"]
    Let memory_utilization be get_memory_utilization with pattern as pattern
    Let network_utilization be get_network_utilization with pattern as pattern
    
    Note: Determine optimal instance size based on utilization
    Let recommended_specs be calculate_optimal_instance_specs with:
        cpu_utilization as cpu_utilization
        memory_utilization as memory_utilization
        network_utilization as network_utilization
        peak_utilization as pattern["peak_utilization"]
        utilization_variance as pattern["utilization_variance"]
        performance_requirements as extract_performance_requirements with resource as resource
    
    Let recommended_instance_type be find_matching_instance_type with:
        specs as recommended_specs
        provider as resource["provider"]
        region as resource["region"]
        pricing_data as pricing_data
    
    Note: Calculate cost impact
    Let current_hourly_cost be pricing_data["instance_types"][current_instance_type]["hourly_cost"]
    Let recommended_hourly_cost be pricing_data["instance_types"][recommended_instance_type]["hourly_cost"]
    Let monthly_hours be 730.0  Note: Average hours per month
    Let monthly_savings be (current_hourly_cost minus recommended_hourly_cost) times monthly_hours
    
    Note: Assess risk and complexity
    Let risk_assessment be assess_rightsizing_risk with:
        current_specs as current_specs
        recommended_specs as recommended_specs
        utilization_pattern as pattern
    
    If monthly_savings is greater than 10.0 and recommended_instance_type is not equal to current_instance_type:
        Return dictionary with:
            "recommendation" as "rightsize"
            "recommended_configuration" as dictionary with:
                "instance_type" as recommended_instance_type
                "specs" as recommended_specs
            "monthly_savings" as monthly_savings
            "complexity" as risk_assessment["complexity"]
            "risk_level" as risk_assessment["risk_level"]
            "prerequisites" as risk_assessment["prerequisites"]
            "confidence_score" as calculate_recommendation_confidence with analysis_data as dictionary with:
                "utilization_variance" as pattern["utilization_variance"]
                "data_points" as pattern["data_point_count"]
                "cost_savings" as monthly_savings
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary with:
            "recommendation" as "no_change"
            "reason" as determine_no_change_reason with savings as monthly_savings and types as [current_instance_type, recommended_instance_type]

Note: Reserved Instance and Savings Plan Optimization
Process called "analyze_reserved_instance_opportunities" that takes data as CloudAccountData and patterns as Dictionary[String, UsagePattern] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Analyze opportunities for reserved instance purchases and savings plans
    Let ri_recommendations be list containing
    Let total_potential_savings be 0.0
    
    Note: Group resources by instance family and region for RI analysis
    Let instance_groups be group_instances_for_ri_analysis with:
        resources as data["resource_inventory"]
        patterns as patterns
    
    For each group_key in keys of instance_groups:
        Let instance_group be instance_groups[group_key]
        Let ri_analysis be analyze_ri_opportunity_for_group with:
            group as instance_group
            billing_history as data["billing_history"]
            provider as extract_provider_from_group_key with key as group_key
        
        If ri_analysis["recommended"]:
            Let optimization_action be OptimizationAction with:
                action_id as generate_action_id
                action_type as RESERVED_INSTANCE_PURCHASE
                affected_resource as group_key
                current_configuration as dictionary with:
                    "payment_model" as "on_demand"
                    "instances" as instance_group
                recommended_configuration as ri_analysis["recommended_ri_configuration"]
                estimated_monthly_savings as ri_analysis["monthly_savings"]
                implementation_complexity as LOW
                risk_level as MINIMAL
                prerequisites as list containing "Budget approval", "Capacity planning review"
                implementation_steps as generate_ri_purchase_steps with analysis as ri_analysis
            
            Add optimization_action to ri_recommendations
            Set total_potential_savings to total_potential_savings plus ri_analysis["monthly_savings"]
    
    Return dictionary with:
        "recommendations" as ri_recommendations
        "potential_savings" as total_potential_savings
        "analysis_metadata" as create_ri_analysis_metadata with groups as instance_groups

Process called "analyze_ri_opportunity_for_group" that takes group as List[orchestrator.MultiCloudResource] and billing_history as List[BillingDataPoint] and provider as orchestrator.CloudProvider returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Analyze reserved instance opportunity for a group of similar instances
    Let total_monthly_hours be calculate_total_monthly_usage with group as group
    Let consistency_score be calculate_usage_consistency with group as group and history as billing_history
    Let on_demand_cost be calculate_on_demand_cost with group as group
    
    Note: Only recommend RI if usage is consistent and substantial
    If consistency_score is greater than 0.8 and total_monthly_hours is greater than 500.0:
        Let ri_options be get_available_ri_options with:
            provider as provider
            instance_types as extract_instance_types with group as group
            region as extract_region with group as group
        
        Let optimal_ri_option be select_optimal_ri_option with:
            options as ri_options
            usage_hours as total_monthly_hours
            on_demand_cost as on_demand_cost
        
        Let ri_cost be calculate_ri_cost with option as optimal_ri_option and hours as total_monthly_hours
        Let monthly_savings be on_demand_cost minus ri_cost
        
        Return dictionary with:
            "recommended" as true
            "recommended_ri_configuration" as optimal_ri_option
            "monthly_savings" as monthly_savings
            "payback_period" as optimal_ri_option["upfront_cost"] divided by monthly_savings
            "confidence_score" as consistency_score
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary with:
            "recommended" as false
            "reason" as determine_ri_rejection_reason with consistency as consistency_score and hours as total_monthly_hours

Note: Automated Cost Governance
Process called "implement_cost_governance_policies" that takes policies as List[CostGovernancePolicy] returns GovernanceImplementationResult:
    Note: Automated cost control with budgets, alerts, and automatic remediation
    Let governance_context be create_governance_context with policies as policies
    
    Note: Implement budget controls
    Let budget_controls be implement_budget_controls with policies as policies and context as governance_context
    
    Note: Setup spending alerts and notifications
    Let spending_alerts be configure_spending_alerts with policies as policies and context as governance_context
    
    Note: Setup automated remediation rules
    Let auto_remediation_rules be setup_cost_remediation_automation with policies as policies and context as governance_context
    
    Note: Implement cost allocation and tracking
    Let cost_allocation_tracking be implement_cost_allocation_tracking with policies as policies and context as governance_context
    
    Note: Setup governance monitoring and reporting
    Let governance_monitoring be setup_governance_monitoring with:
        policies as policies
        budget_controls as budget_controls
        alerts as spending_alerts
        remediation as auto_remediation_rules
        allocation as cost_allocation_tracking
    
    Return GovernanceImplementationResult with:
        success as true
        active_policies as policies
        budget_controls as budget_controls
        alert_configurations as spending_alerts
        remediation_rules as auto_remediation_rules
        cost_tracking as cost_allocation_tracking
        monitoring_configuration as governance_monitoring
        governance_dashboard as create_cost_governance_dashboard with:
            policies as policies
            budgets as budget_controls
            alerts as spending_alerts
            monitoring as governance_monitoring

Process called "implement_budget_controls" that takes policies as List[CostGovernancePolicy] and context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns List[BudgetControl]:
    Note: Implement automated budget controls with enforcement mechanisms
    Let budget_controls be list containing
    
    For each policy in policies:
        If policy["type"] is equal to "budget_enforcement":
            Let budget_control be BudgetControl with:
                control_id as generate_control_id
                policy_id as policy["policy_id"]
                budget_amount as policy["budget_amount"]
                enforcement_level as policy["enforcement_level"]
                time_period as policy["time_period"]
                scope as policy["scope"]
                thresholds as policy["alert_thresholds"]
                actions as policy["enforcement_actions"]
                monitoring_frequency as policy["monitoring_frequency"]
                created_at as get_current_timestamp
            
            Note: Setup budget monitoring
            Let monitoring_config be setup_budget_monitoring with:
                control as budget_control
                context as context
            
            Set budget_control["monitoring_configuration"] to monitoring_config
            
            Note: Configure enforcement actions
            Let enforcement_config be configure_budget_enforcement with:
                control as budget_control
                context as context
            
            Set budget_control["enforcement_configuration"] to enforcement_config
            
            Add budget_control to budget_controls
    
    Return budget_controls

Note: Cost Anomaly Detection
Process called "detect_cost_anomalies" that takes data as CloudAccountData and context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: AI-powered cost anomaly detection with machine learning algorithms
    Let anomaly_detection_engine be initialize_anomaly_detection_engine with context as context
    Let cost_history be data["billing_history"]
    let anomalies be list containing
    
    Note: Detect spending anomalies using multiple algorithms
    Let statistical_anomalies be detect_statistical_anomalies with:
        history as cost_history
        engine as anomaly_detection_engine
    
    Let ml_anomalies be detect_ml_based_anomalies with:
        history as cost_history
        engine as anomaly_detection_engine
    
    Let pattern_anomalies be detect_pattern_based_anomalies with:
        history as cost_history
        engine as anomaly_detection_engine
    
    Note: Correlate and deduplicate anomalies
    Let correlated_anomalies be correlate_anomalies with:
        statistical as statistical_anomalies
        ml_based as ml_anomalies
        pattern_based as pattern_anomalies
    
    Note: Assess anomaly severity and business impact
    For each anomaly in correlated_anomalies:
        Let severity_assessment be assess_anomaly_severity with:
            anomaly as anomaly
            account_data as data
            context as context
        
        Set anomaly["severity"] to severity_assessment["severity"]
        Set anomaly["business_impact"] to severity_assessment["business_impact"]
        Set anomaly["recommended_actions"] to severity_assessment["recommended_actions"]
        
        Add anomaly to anomalies
    
    Return dictionary with:
        "anomalies" as anomalies
        "risk_score" as calculate_anomaly_risk_score with anomalies as anomalies
        "detection_metadata" as create_detection_metadata with engine as anomaly_detection_engine

Note: Utility Functions and Helpers
Type called "CostGovernancePolicy":
    policy_id as String
    policy_name as String
    type as String
    budget_amount as Float
    enforcement_level as String
    time_period as String
    scope as Dictionary[String, Any]
    alert_thresholds as List[Float]
    enforcement_actions as List[String]
    monitoring_frequency as String

Type called "BudgetControl":
    control_id as String
    policy_id as String
    budget_amount as Float
    enforcement_level as String
    time_period as String
    scope as Dictionary[String, Any]
    thresholds as List[Float]
    actions as List[String]
    monitoring_frequency as String
    monitoring_configuration as Dictionary[String, Any]
    enforcement_configuration as Dictionary[String, Any]
    created_at as Integer

Type called "GovernanceImplementationResult":
    success as Boolean
    active_policies as List[CostGovernancePolicy]
    budget_controls as List[BudgetControl]
    alert_configurations as Dictionary[String, Any]
    remediation_rules as Dictionary[String, Any]
    cost_tracking as Dictionary[String, Any]
    monitoring_configuration as Dictionary[String, Any]
    governance_dashboard as Dictionary[String, Any]

Process called "generate_action_id" returns String:
    Return "cost_opt_" with message get_current_timestamp with message "_" with message generate_random_suffix

Process called "generate_control_id" returns String:
    Return "budget_ctrl_" with message get_current_timestamp with message "_" with message generate_random_suffix

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current Unix timestamp in seconds
    Return 1640995200

Process called "generate_random_suffix" returns String:
    Return "xyz789"  Note: In production, would generate actual random string

Process called "create_cost_analysis_context" that takes account_data as CloudAccountData returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary with:
        "account_id" as account_data["account_id"]
        "provider" as account_data["provider"]
        "analysis_timestamp" as get_current_timestamp
        "resource_count" as length of account_data["resource_inventory"]
        "billing_history_months" as length of account_data["billing_history"]
        "analysis_scope" as "comprehensive"

Process called "keys" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, Any] returns List[String]:
    Return list containing "key1", "key2"  Note: In production, would return actual keys

Process called "find_resource_by_id" that takes resources as List[orchestrator.MultiCloudResource] and id as String returns Optional[orchestrator.MultiCloudResource]:
    For each resource in resources:
        If resource["resource_id"] is equal to id:
            Return resource
    Return None

Process called "take_first_n" that takes list as List[Any] and n as Integer returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    Let max_items be (n if n is less than length of list else length of list)
    
    For i from 0 to (max_items minus 1):
        Add list at index i to result
    
    Return result